important kubernetes command:-

kubectl run firstpod --image=nginx

kubectl get pods

kubectl describe pod firstpod

kubectl exec -it -- /bin/bash

kubectl delete pod firstpod

kubectl get pod firstpod -o yaml

kubectl create -f firstpod.yml

kubectl exec -it firstpod --container db -- /bin/bash //This will actually go into the container if multiple containers are launched in a pod

kubectl delete all --all //delete all pods

kubectl delete -f firstpod.yml //whatever containers present in the yml file will be deleted

kubectl get all --show-labels

kubectl get pods -l app=fp //label based selection

kubectl create ns firstns //creating namespace

kubectl create -f firstpod.yml --namespace=firstns //creating a pod under firstns namespace

kubectl get pods --namespace firstns //fetching all pods under firstns namespace

kubectl config set-context --current --namespace firstns // kubernetes config changes

kubectl create -f firstpod.yml --dry-run=client //do a dry run on a client

kubectl explain pod //shows documentation for pod

Three ways to access kubernetes cluster
- Dashboard
- Command line (kubectl command)
- Rest API


minikube dashboard --opens the kubernetes dashboard

kubectl get deployments -- get all deployments from kubernetes

kubectl replace -f webserver.yml -- replace the deployment

kubectl describe deploy mywebserver -- describe the deployment

kubectl rollout history deployment -- history of deployment

kubectl rollout history deployment mywebserver --revision=2  --shows information of a particular rollout

kubectl rollout undo deployment mywebserver --to-revision=1 --rolling back a particular deployment

kubectl scale deployment mywebserver --replicas=20 --manual scaling 

kubectl get pv -- lists down the persistent volume

kubectl create -f demo-persistent-volume.yml -- creating a persistent volume

kubectl create -f docker-mysql-configmap.yml,docker-mysql-deployment.yml,docker-mysql-service.yml

kubectl create -f coupon-service-deployment.yml,coupon-service-svc.yml

kubectl create -f product-service-deployment.yml,product-service-svc.yml